    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Airlines Flying Nonstop from New York to Miami</h2><ul><li><strong>American Airlines</strong> — Dominant on this route with multiple daily nonstop flights from JFK, LGA, and EWR to MIA</li><li><strong>Delta Air Lines</strong> — Multiple daily from JFK and LGA to MIA and FLL (Fort Lauderdale)</li><li><strong>JetBlue</strong> — Multiple daily from JFK to MIA, with Mint premium options</li><li><strong>Spirit Airlines</strong> — Budget nonstop option from LGA to MIA, often the cheapest available fare</li><li><strong>Frontier Airlines</strong> — Budget nonstop service with very low base fares</li><li><strong>United</strong> — Daily service from EWR to MIA</li></ul><h2>Tips for New York to Miami Nonstop</h2><p>This is one of the easiest nonstop routes to find a cheap fare on, given the intense competition. Spirit and Frontier consistently undercut legacy carriers by 0–150 each way. For a 3-hour flight, the trade-off is worth it for most budget travelers.</p><div class='info-box'><p>ℹ️ Fort Lauderdale (FLL) is 30 minutes from Miami by car and served by even more budget carriers. If you're staying in Miami Beach, FLL is often cheaper and nearly as convenient.</p></div><ul><li>Book at least 3 weeks ahead for winter holiday travel — New York to Miami spikes in price dramatically in December and March (spring break).</li><li>Spirit and Frontier fares look cheap but add bag and seat fees — calculate the total cost before booking.</li></ul>
